title: Static Analysis

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows an application to view configuration of the local Bluetooth phone and to make and accept connections with paired devices.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

Broadcast Receiver (uk.nhs.nhsx.covid19.android.app.exposure.encounter.ExposureNotificationBroadcastReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.gms.nearby.exposurenotification.EXPOSURE_CALLBACK
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

strings: "about" : "About the NHS Test and Trace app"
"about_common_questions_text" : "Visit our common questions page to learn more about the NHS Test & Trace app, the official NHS QR codes for venue check in, and the wider Test & Trace programme."

"about_how_this_app_works_text" : "This app uses contact tracing technology to help protect yourself and others.

The app detects and logs other nearby app users. If any of those users later test positive for coronavirus, you will receive an alert with advice.

The app also lets you report your symptoms and find out if you need a test.

You can also use this app to scan official NHS QR codes to check in to places you visit."
"about_our_policies_text" : "Our policy documentation tells you important information about using the app, how we use your data, and how the app supports user access."

"about_software_information_text" : "App name: %1$s
Version: %2$s
Date of release: %3$s

Entity name and address:
NHS Test & Trace
Department of Health and Social Care
39 Victoria Street
Westminster
London
SW1H 0EU
UK"

"about_your_data_text" : "The app has access to the postcode district you added in the registration, a history of venues you have checked into in the last 21 days, your last test result and the start date of your symptoms. You can delete the stored data."

"authentication_auth_code_rationale" : "Please enter one code above. You will have received this code by letter or by email, and it will look like this:

5apv-enka

Please note, this app is for use by people aged 18 years and over only."

"authentication_message" : "The app plays a critical part in the NHS Test & Trace service. The more people that use it, the more we can improve it.

While we wait for a vaccine to be found, NHS Test & Trace and the app are the best way for us to get back to the things we love."
"authentication_title" : "Thank you for helping us improve the NHS COVID-19 app"
"common_google_play_services_enable_text" : "%1$s won't work unless you enable Google Play services."

"common_google_play_services_updating_text" : "%1$s won't run without Google Play services, which are currently updating."
"common_google_play_services_wear_update_text" : "New version of Google Play services needed. It will update itself shortly."

"delete_data_explanation" : "Any information you share through this app will only be used for public health purposes. Data held will be removed once you confirm. Please not that your phone will retain some information, such as the data your phone collects to log other user app users. This data is not controlled by the app but by your phone’s operating system. If you want to continue using this app later, you will have to set it up again."

"enable_bluetooth_rationale" : "If you have Bluetooth turned off, this app will not work.

This app uses battery-saving Bluetooth Low Energy to determine when it is near another phone with this app installed.

This app cannot track your location and your privacy remains protected.

Please go to Settings and turn on Bluetooth."
"enable_bluetooth_title" : "Bluetooth always needs to be kept on"

"enable_exposure_notifications_rationale" : "To identify whether you are at risk of infection, you must activate the Exposure Notifications feature.

Exposure Logging works by your device receiving, via Bluetooth, encrypted random IDs of other users and passing your own random ID to their devices. This feature can be deactivated at any time, but the app will not then work."
"enable_exposure_notifications_title" : "For this app to work, you must allow Exposure Notifications"

"enable_location_service_rationale" : "To make Bluetooth work, we need you to turn on location services on your phone.

This app is not using Bluetooth or your location to track you. Your personal identity will remain protected at all times.

If you do not enable location services on your phone this app will not work.

To enable this app to work, please go to Settings and enable location services."
"enable_location_service_title" : "You need to enable location services on your phone"
"expiration_notification_description_passed" : "You have been released from isolation since the %s at 23:59"
"expiration_temperature_hint" : "However, if you have a high temperature, continue to self-isolate until it returns to normal"
"exposure_notification_hint" : "You have been near an app user who has coronavirus. Please stay at home to keep yourself and others safe."

"exposure_notification_recommendation" : "You are at high risk of having and spreading the virus even if you don’t have any symptoms.

Your isolation countdown has started and you should self-isolate for the full period identified.

For further advice, please visit:"

"exposure_notifications_rationale" : "This app uses the Exposure Notifications framework by Google to let you know if you have come into contact with any other app users who tested positive for coronavirus."
"how_to_scan_qr_code" : "How to scan an official NHS QR code"
"isolate_after_corona_virus_symptoms" : "Your symptoms suggest you might have coronavirus. Please isolate yourself and your household and book a free test."

"message_no_coronavirus_symptoms" : "If you develop any of these symptoms, report them on this app and book a free test.

For further advice, please visit:"
"more_info_content_description" : "More information about postcode district risk alerts"
"mtrl_picker_toggle_to_day_selection" : "Tap to switch to selecting a day"
"mtrl_picker_toggle_to_year_selection" : "Tap to switch to selecting a year"

"onboarding_check_symptoms_text" : "Feeling unwell? Check if your symptoms could be coronavirus and order a free test if you need one."
"onboarding_eighteen_plus" : "Remember: this app is for people aged 18 years and over."

"onboarding_exposure_notifications_description" : "This app uses Google’s ‘Exposure Notifications’ framework to let you know if you have come into contact with other app users who have reported a positive test for Coronavirus. For the app to work, you must allow Exposure Notifications."
"onboarding_isolation_countdown_text" : "If you are isolating, the app will count down the days and give you the right information."
"onboarding_not_final_notice" : "Please note that this is a test version of the app for clinical investigation and improvement and is not the final version."
"onboarding_notifications_text" : "Find out when you've been near other app users who have reported a positive test for coronavirus."

"onboarding_privacy_control_text" : "The NHS values your privacy. The app tracks the virus, it doesn't track you and cannot see who you are, where you are or who is with you. Any information is stored on your phone, not in a central database. That means that if you test positive for coronavirus, you can choose to share your data with the NHS so we can alert other app users. You can be sure that personal data never leaves your phone and you remain anonymous at all times."

"onboarding_privacy_your_data_text1" : "You also control your data. The app stores your data for 14 days after it’s been recorded (and for 21 days for the venues you check into with QR code). You can delete your data at any time by choosing 'delete all my data' or by uninstalling the app. Your phone may still keep some very basic data generated by the app - this is controlled by your phone's operating system, not by the NHS."
"onboarding_privacy_your_data_text2" : "This app uses automated decision-making. This means that people do not make decisions. Therefore no one sees your data."
"onboarding_subtitle" : "It's like having Test and Trace in your pocket. Here are some of the useful things you can do with the app:"

"onboarding_venue_check_in_text" : "Check into places like bars and restaurants with the app's QR code scanner, without having to fill out any forms. If coronavirus is found at the venue, the app will let you know."
"onboarding_welcome_title" : "This app helps us keep each other safe"

"post_code_rationale" : "The postcode district helps with learning about the spread of coronavirus in different areas. This makes sure we can give the best possible public health advice for your area.

Don’t worry. Your postcode district won’t be used to track your location."
"post_code_rationale_title" : "Why do we need the postcode district?"
"post_code_title" : "Enter the first part of your postcode (postcode district)"

"qr_code_failure_description" : "It could be that you are trying to scan an invalid official NHS QR code or that this venue isn’t recognised.

Please check in to the venue manually. Speak to a member of staff at the venue for more information."

"qr_code_how_it_helps_text" : "This app feature makes it easy for businesses to support contact tracing.

It helps you and others (as well as the venue) stay safe while keeping your privacy protected."

"qr_code_how_it_works_text" : "This app uses official NHS QR codes to help you quickly and easily check into places you visit.

By using this app, we can alert you if you may have come into contact with the virus at a venue you visited recently."
"qr_code_permission_denied_subtitle" : "This app uses your camera to check in to venues. Please allow camera permissions to scan the official NHS QR code."
"qr_code_permission_denied_title" : "Check in to a venue by scanning an official NHS QR code"

"qr_code_scan_explanation" : "Hold your phone so that the official NHS QR code appears in the viewfinder above. When your phone recognises the QR code, it will show that you have successfully checked in."

"qr_code_success_subtitle" : "Thank you for scanning, you have now checked in.
You will be automatically checked out at midnight or when you scan another official NHS QR code."
"qr_code_unsupported_description" : "Please check in to the venue manually. Speak to a member of staff at the venue for more information."
"qr_code_unsupported_title" : "Sorry, your phone doesn’t support venue check-in"

"state_test_positive_rationale_1" : "Your test result indicates that you have coronavirus. You have been sent an email or text with more information. If you need further advice, please visit the link."

"tablet_support_description" : "Your device seems to be a tablet. This app is only available for smartphones because the app is only effective if you have it on a device that is with you all the time when you go out. Please install the app on your smartphone."
"tablet_support_title" : "This app is made for mobile smartphones"
"test_ordering_description_1" : "Selecting ‘Book a free test now’ will redirect you from this app to the government’s coronavirus testing website."

"test_ordering_description_2" : "Once there, you’ll be asked to enter some personal details (like your address) in order to get a test, but nothing you enter there will be shared with this app, and nothing you’ve entered here will be shared there."
"test_ordering_description_3" : "The only information shared between app and website is a digital ‘token’ which will help us get your test results back to the app."
